This is a quick description on how KDE Frameworks packaging is done.

 * Ensure everything is green in build.kde.org
 * ssh -A scripty@l10n.kde.org, and from there:
    cd ~/frameworks_packaging/release-tools/
    git pull
    rm -rf sources versions REVISIONS_AND_HASHES l10n tags.git
 * Update version file with the correct version number
    (ask Alex Merry if in doubt about making a new ECM release, after git diff v1.last.0..)
 * Edit config, ensure dry_run=0
 * cd ../src ; ./kdesrc-build --src-only ; cd ../release-tools ; ./list_frameworks.sh
 * Pack the sources:
     ./update_l10n.sh ; ./make_rc_tag.sh
      (then locally, try compiling the rc tag -> git fetch --tags ; kdesrc-build extra-cmake-modules frameworks)
     ./pack_all.sh

 * If you have ssh access to ftpadmin@depot.kde.org:
     ./upload_all.sh

 * Inform release-team@kde.org, attaching REVISIONS_AND_HASHES

 * To update a tag+tarball after making fixes (grabbing all changes from master)
     (this is the lazy version of the next solution, it re-commits all po files so it's not as good)
     ./make_rc_tag.sh kconfigwidgets && ./pack.sh kconfigwidgets && ./upload_all.sh
     (and re-run ./create_sources_inc if already done)

 * To update a tag+tarball by cherry-picking a single fix
     git checkout local_release ; git fetch ; git cherry-pick -x sha1 (or git merge origin/master) ; git tag -a vx.y.z-rcN -m "<message>" ; git push --tags
     Update N in tags.git, ./pack.sh <module> ; ./upload_all.sh
     (and re-run ./create_sources_inc if already done)

 * cat versions/* > REVISIONS_AND_HASHES, if you want to send it all-in-one-go after updates

 * Write the list of changes in markdown format, into a file called changelog (here),
   send it to kde-frameworks-devel@kde.org for information and review.
   Example syntax: (remove the indentation)

        ### KActivities

        * reimplementation of the file item plugin for linking files to activities

Several days later:
 * chmod a+rx on the FTP directory, 8 hours before the release
 ./tag_all.sh
 ./create_sources_inc
   (paste the output into files as requested)
 cd ../www_info ; svn commit ; cd ../www_announcements ; svn commit

 * Email changelog text to kde-devel@kde.org and kde-core-devel@kde.org
 * TODO: automate social media stuff

 * Update the version numbers right away in master.
     vi version
     ./increase_frameworks_version.sh step1 ; wait for CI ; ./increase_frameworks_version.sh step2

